  "texts": [
    "Specifically, we examine how the length of the prompts and their position (i.e., prepend vs. append) affect the model's accuracy.",
    "Note that all results for this subsection are from FT-Seq (BERT) with DELD.Prompt Length: We experimented with various prompt lengths, ranging from 4 to 20 tokens, and observed their impact on the model's performance.",
    "The results, shown in Table III, indicate that prompt length significantly affects the detection accuracy.From the results, we observe that:• 4-Token Prompts: Achieve moderate accuracy, with an average of 81.0%.",
    "• 8-Token Prompts: Show a slight improvement, with an average accuracy of 82.2%.",
    "• 12-Token Prompts: Perform the best overall, achieving the highest average accuracy of 85.2%."
  ]
}